aS'Erk, under the new ruling, will be able to tell jurors about the\xc2\xa0"loss of earning capacity" suffered by the family because of Jackson\'s death. \xc2\xa0This means the jury can consider the Jackson argument that he\xc2\xa0could have earned millions with a clothing line, endorsements and movies. The expert\'s estimate that Jackson would have completed five world tours before he was 65, if he had lived, can also be considered.'
